The defendant Tracey Jeanette Muniz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tracey Jeanette Muniz is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

Defendant Tracey Jeanette Muniz not in court.   No Assistant District Attorney Available appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The victim Janelle J. present in court. The victim submitted a restitution work sheet. Court grant the victim's request for restitution in the amount of $2,524.24 to be taken out of bail on deposit, if any; and the balance to be paid during the period of the probationary period.  Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment.

Statements made as to Sentencing by both counsel and the Defendant.  Additional statement made by the victim Janelle J.

AS TO COUNT 1:    Defendant sentenced to serve  90 DAYS in the House of Correction (HOC) with credit for 2 days time served.  Huber privileges under Sec.303.08 Wis. Stats. to apply for work and child care.

Court IMPOSED AND STAYED the sentence and placed Defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS with the following conditions:
*  Pay a fine of $300.00 inclusive of costs with the exception of the DNA fee to be paid out of bail on deposit, if any; and the balance due prior to the end of the probationary period.  Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.
*  Maintain employment.
*  ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
*  AODA assessment with follow up care and treatment.
*  Random urine screens with no positive results.
*  Participate in any anger management courses and cooperate fully.
*  Cooperate with agent.
*  No new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.
*  Defendant required to provide a biological specimen (DNA) to the State Crime Lab for testing.

Restitution Hearing scheduled for 11-03-2016 at 08:30 am in Branch 45.

Court WILL consider expungement if Defendant successfully completes all conditions of probation with no new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.
